Package io.xmljim.algorithms.model.util

Class SerialTemporal

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Number
io.xmljim.algorithms.model.util.SerialTemporal
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<SerialTemporal>
Direct Known Subclasses:
SerialDate, SerialDateTime
public abstract class SerialTemporal
extends Number
implements Comparable<SerialTemporal>
The base, abstract class for serializing dates and date-times to a numeric representation. All subclasses of this class extend from Number, which allow for use as Scalar values

    • ofSeconds

      public static SerialTemporal ofSeconds​(long epochSeconds)
      Evaluates the epoch seconds and creates an instance based on the modulus of the seconds. If the modulus of epoch seconds to number of seconds within a day is 0, then it will be converted to a date, otherwise to a date-time
      Parameters:
      epochSeconds - the number of seconds since January 1, 1970
      Returns:
      a new SerialTemporal instance
